==English==
===Etymology 1===
{{L.}} ''[[peregrinari]]'' "to live or travel abroad"

====Pronunciation====
* ''(US)'' /ˈpɛrɪɡrɪˌnet/

====Verb====
{{en-verb|peregrinate|peregrinates|peregrinated|peregrinating}}
# {{intransitive}} To travel from place to place, or from one country to another, especially on foot; hence, to sojourn in foreign countries.
#{{transitive}} To [[travel]] through a specific place.

====Related terms====
* [[pilgrim]]

====Derived terms====
* [[peregrination]]

